[[Zulrah]] is a level 725 solo-only snake boss found at a shrine east of [[Zul-Andra]], accessible by boat. Zulrah's shrine can be exited through victory, death, logout/hopping worlds, or teleportation.

== Requirements ==

* Completion of {{SCP|Quest}} [[Regicide]] to access Zul-Andra

==Recommended skills==
*{{SCP|Magic|75+}}(if using Magic)
*{{SCP|Ranged|80+}}(if using Ranged)
*{{SCP|Defence|70+}}
*{{SCP|Hitpoints|80+}}
*{{SCP|Prayer|45+}} for [[Eagle Eye]], [[Mystic Might]], and [[Protection prayers]]
*{{SCP|Construction|82+}} (In order to boost for [[Ornate rejuvenation pool]])

==Transportation==
*A [[Zul-andra teleport]] scroll will take you directly next to the dock, which is about 20 seconds faster than using the Fairy ring. Despite their high cost, they are worth using once you are able to kill Zulrah consistently without as many deaths, because the price is offset by the extra kills per hour.
*The [[Fairy ring (Construction)|fairy ring]] (code {{Fairycode|BJS}}) to the [[Zul-Andra]] stepping stone, requiring level 76 [[Agility]] (can be boosted). Quick fairy ring access:
**Inside the [[Player-owned house]] with a [[Fairy ring (Construction)|built Fairy ring]]
**Outside the [[Legends' Guild]] (via [[Quest point cape]])
**Outside the [[Fremennik Slayer Dungeon]] (via [[Slayer ring]])
**Next to the [[Salve Graveyard Teleport]]
*A [[Charter ship]] to [[Tyras Camp]], requiring 3,200 coins (1,600 with [[Cabin Fever]]/[[Ring of Charos]] or 800 with both).
Due to the high damage the boss can deal and shorter trip lengths, having access to a continuous source of healing is helpful to continue fighting the boss quickly. 

* An [[Ornate rejuvenation pool]] in a [[Player-owned house]] can quickly cure venom and restore prayer and hitpoints.
* The [[Pool of Refreshment]] in the [[Ferox Enclave]] can be quickly accessed with a [[Ring of dueling]].

==Forms==
[[File:Fighting Zulrah.png|thumb|300px|right|A player fights Zulrah, the serpent of the [[Poison Waste]], in its tanzanite form.]]
Throughout the fight, [[Zulrah]] will continually dive into the swamp, sending out a plethora of attacks before doing so. It will then re-emerge in its next phase and continue its attacks, usually as a different form.

If struck with a hit just as it dives, the hit will register on Zulrah shortly after it resurfaces. Unlike the [[Alchemical Hydra]], Zulrah's existing attacks will cause damage even after it is killed, so it is important to keep health and the appropriate prayer up to avoid an accidental death.

Zulrah has a Defence, Magic, and Ranged level of 300, along with +50 ranged and magical accuracy and strength bonus on all forms. Although Zulrah has no melee defence in any form, Zulrah can only be reached with a halberd-type weapon. The ranged and magic attacks will envenom the player unless they miss, even if blocked by a protection prayer. Damage dealt to Zulrah is capped at 50, with hits dealing more than that randomly hitting it for 45-50 damage.

[[File:Zulrah (serpentine).png|left|50px]]
* Zulrah's '''{{Colour|green|green}}''' form, in which it will attack with [[Ranged]], with a few exceptions such as its "[[TzTok-Jad|Jad]]" phase (see rotations). While in this form, Zulrah is '''weak to magical''' attacks - possessing -45 magic defence and +50 ranged defence.
{{clear|left}}
[[File:Zulrah (magma).png|left|50px]]
* Zulrah's '''{{Colour|red|crimson}}''' form, in which it will attack with [[Melee]]. Zulrah will stare at the player's position for several seconds before whipping its tail at that area. If the player does not move away from the targeted area in time, they will be dealt 20-30 damage and be [[Stun (status)|stunned]] for several seconds. While in this form, Zulrah is '''weak to magical''' attacks - possessing +0 magic defence and +300 ranged defence.
{{clear|left}}
[[File:Zulrah (tanzanite).png|left|50px]]
* Zulrah's '''{{Colour|#008FFF|tanzanite}}''' form, in which it will randomly attack with both [[Magic]] and [[Ranged]] attacks, although it uses magic much more frequently compared to ranged. While in this form, Zulrah is '''weak to ranged''' attacks - possessing +300 magic defence and +0 ranged defence.
{{clear|left}}

==Special attacks==
During the fight, Zulrah can summon [[snakeling]]s and/or [[venom]] clouds in ''any'' form, however the phase at which it does so, as well as when during the phase, is predetermined by the rotation.

===Snakelings===
[[File:Snakeling.png|100px|left]]
Snakelings are monsters that Zulrah will summon during the fight via shooting white orbs. Each snakeling attacks with either magic or melee, but never both. Despite their combat level of 90, they have extremely low defence and only 1 [[Hitpoint]]; this is made up for by their incredibly accurate attacks, which can hit up to 15.

Protection prayers block their attacks; however, it is better to tank the snakelings' attacks if Zulrah is also attacking, since Zulrah can deal more damage, and it is nearly impossible to flick multiple snakelings and Zulrah attacking together. '''It is highly recommended to bring a [[ring of recoil]] or [[ring of suffering|ring of suffering(r/ri)]] to kill the snakelings.'''

While most snakelings spawn immediately, in some of Zulrah's attack rotations it will occasionally throw a white orb and then dive into the swamp. The summoned snakeling will only appear '''after''' Zulrah reemerges from the swamp.

If you are hiding from Zulrah, it is best to use this time to kill the snakelings to lessen the need to eat and/or use [[ring of recoil|recoil]] charges during the fight.

Snakelings will also die off if they have been lingering around for more than 40 seconds, whether they are in combat with the player or not, although this generally occurs when the snakeling is stuck and cannot reach the player. They will automatically die off with Zulrah when it is killed.

[[File:Venom_cloud.png|thumb|300px|right|A player taking damage from Zulrah's venom clouds.]]

===Venom clouds===
[[Zulrah]] will spawn venomous clouds during the fight via a barrage of dark-green orbs. If a player stands within a cloud's 3x3 area, they will be dealt varying damage per [[tick]] which can add up quickly. Players will want to position themselves accordingly for each phase as to minimise the potential damage from these clouds.

Certain phases may force the player to run through venom clouds in order to re-position themselves. Doing so will deal some damage to the player, however, this is a much better outcome than the potential damage inflicted by an unprepared Zulrah attack.

Similarly to the snakeling orbs, if Zulrah launches a dark-green orb just as it dives, the venomous cloud will not appear until Zulrah resurfaces.

While these clouds inflict [[venom]] damage, they '''do not''' envenom the player.

==Setup==
The best setup uses both [[Ranged]] and [[Magic]] to exploit Zulrah's weaknesses. 

Due to Zulrah's weaknesses, lower-levelled players (or higher ones with the [[Harmonised nightmare staff]]) are encouraged to use fire spells, as they are 50% more accurate and deal 50% more damage to Zulrah. Powered staves don't have this benefit, and Zulrah's low defences in its green form make the spells fairly accurate.

Beginners may find it easier to bring fewer Magic/Ranged switches until they are comfortable with Zulrah's mechanics and phases. 

A [[Serpentine helm]] is very useful for its immunity to [[venom]], despite it having negative Magic and Ranged bonuses. It prevents the need for [[anti-venom+]] potions, therefore freeing up an inventory slot, but over time it's less cost efficient than the potions, considering it needs to be charged with [[Zulrah's scales]]. It's recommended for beginners to wear the Serpentine helm until they are able to kill Zulrah consistently. Players who can kill Zulrah consistently and efficiently can forgo the helm, as they will be using the house and fairy ring method to return to the boss.

