Melee=
The [[Noxious halberd]] is powerful enough to be used on all 3 phases to great effect. The [[Crystal halberd]] special attack is very effective during the last hit of each phase, as the double hitsplats get around the 50 damage cap on Zulrah. Attacking primarily with the crystal halberd is possible, but significantly less effective than simply using other styles, due to its slow attack speed. A small Ranged switch is recommended to bring as some phases cannot be attacked with melee due to poison clouds obstructing the area, and to fit in extra hits with a faster weapon. The [[Eclipse atlatl]] is best suited to this, as it scales very well from the already worn melee gear, although other options from the ranged gear tab can work in its place with one or two additional switches.<br>'''Note:''' No other halberd besides the Noxious halberd (and the Crystal halberd for the special attack) is worth using to melee Zulrah due to the slow 7 tick attack speed of other halberds. If other styles are particularly poor for your available gear, the crystal halberd can still be worth using however.
