==Fight overview==
{{Tile markers box|Module:Tile markers/Zulrah.json}}

All damage towards [[Zulrah]] is capped at 50; if players would have dealt over 50 damage to Zulrah, it is reduced to 45-50 damage.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/844675662631899136|date=22 March 2017|archiveurl=https://reldo.runescape.wiki/i/108141|archivedate=29 May 2020|quote=I think any number you roll over 50 [at Zulrah] is replaced with a random number between 45 and 50.}} Despite this, using the [[twisted bow]] with [[dragon arrows]] is still recommended, as dealing above 50 damage more often will result in more hits dealing 45-50 damage, and still increase the average damage output.

At the start of the fight, Zulrah will be in one of four possible rotations (see chart), with each rotation consisting of predefined phases. It takes Zulrah about three minutes to complete each full rotation. After it finishes a rotation, Zulrah will then begin a new one; it is possible to be the same rotation as the previous one. All rotations after the first one have a chance for Zulrah to randomly be in a phase different from the expected phase. There is also a chance for Zulrah to enter a form where it will randomly switch between mage and ranged attacks in a way that cannot be predicted and prayed against (unlike the "[[Jad]]" phase, which alternates between Magic and Ranged each attack). Because of this, it is best to try to kill Zulrah within the first rotation.

Each column in the chart corresponds to one of Zulrah's rotations, with each row corresponding to that rotation's phase. The green, red, and blue circles indicate Zulrah's form and position in each phase. The "x" represents where to run, and the [[RuneScape:Tile markers|tile markers]] above correspond to these locations. Ensure the camera's orientation is pointed '''south''' to better align with the images.

It is recommended to always use [[Protect from Missiles]] (green form) or [[Protect from Magic]] (tanzanite form) when learning Zulrah, as its attacks are very accurate and often hit hard. The only exception is its green "Jad" phase, which requires alternating between Protect from Missiles and Protect from Magic after every attack it performs. Not every phase has Zulrah attacking the player, however, it is only recommended to disable these prayers once the player is comfortable with the fight's rotations. Zulrah's attacks are capable of hitting up to 41, and with the high damage of the [[snakeling]]s, can easily combo a player in seconds.

Beginners may want to stop attacking or healing during the "Jad" phase and simply focus on praying correctly. As with most attacks in the game, a protection prayer only needs to be active '''starting''' on the same tick that Zulrah begins its attack animation. This means that as soon as a green ranged projectile is fired, overhead prayer should switch back to Protect from Magic. As soon as a red magic projectile is fired, overhead prayer should switch back to Protect from Missiles. The projectile may hit the character while the opposite prayer is active, but 0 damage will occur as long as the correct prayer was active at the start of Zulrah's attack animation.

If Zulrah dies just as it launches an attack, the attack '''can still deal damage''', and can potentially kill the player.

===All rotations===
[[File:Zulrah's_Shrine.png|thumb|300px|Zulrah's Shrine, with Zulrah in its starting phase.]]
At the start of the fight, Zulrah will ''always'' be in its green form in the middle of the shrine. It will never attack directly at the start; rather, Zulrah will fill the area with [[venom]] clouds, leaving the tips on the east and west sides clear. After filling up the area with venom clouds, Zulrah will dive into the swamp and continue on to one of the four rotations.
[[File:Zulrah safespot.png|thumb|right|300px|A safespot to evade Zulrah's melee form, highlighted in yellow. The other safespot is in the equivalent space beside the other pillar.]]
At the end of every rotation, Zulrah will once again appear in the middle of the shrine in its green form. It will attack the player with ranged attacks several times before filling the area with venom clouds. '''This phase counts as the first phase of the new rotation.'''

[[File:Zulrah Patterns.png|thumb|A Zulrah rotation guide, designed to be kept open alongside the game. Each column is a different rotation.]]

===Shared rotations===
====Rotations 1 & 2 ("Crimson A & B")====
After filling the shrine with [[venom]] clouds, Zulrah dives back into the swamp and reappears in the same spot in its crimson form. It will use two [[melee]] attacks before diving back down, appearing at the same spot in its tanzanite form.

When it performs enough attacks in its tanzanite form, Zulrah dives back into the swamp, and the rotations separate until the second-to-last phase in the rotation.

In this second-to-last phase, informally known as the "[[Jad]]" phase, Zulrah appears to the west in a green form. '''It will alternate between [[ranged]] and [[mage]] attacks, starting with ranged.''' Players are advised to switch between [[Protect from Missiles]] and [[Protect from Magic]] on each attack accordingly, otherwise they can be dealt high amounts of damage in a short amount of time. At the end of this phase, Zulrah fills the shrine with venom clouds, leaving the tips on both sides clear of them. <!--Check to see if this is true for rot 1 and 2, end of jad phase. one tip will not be clear no??-->

For the final phase, Zulrah appears in the middle in its crimson form and uses two melee attacks. It will then continue on to the starting phase of the next rotation, in which it appears in the middle in its green form and attacks the player with ranged attacks.

====Rotations 3 & 4 ("Serp & Tanz")====
In these rotations, Zulrah's initial phases are different, though the last three phases are similar to each other.

In Rotation 3, right before the second-to-last phase, Zulrah will send out [[snakeling]]s; this does not occur in Rotation 4. Regardless, the mechanics are still the same in that phase.

In the second-to-last phase, informally known as the "[[Jad]]" phase, Zulrah appears to the east in its green form. '''It will alternate between [[magic]] and [[ranged]] attacks, starting with magic.''' Players are advised to switch between [[Protect from Magic]] and [[Protect from Missiles]] on each attack accordingly, otherwise they can be dealt high amounts of damage in a short amount of time. Zulrah does not send out venom clouds at the end of this phase and simply dives back into the swamp when it's done attacking.

For the final phase of these rotations, Zulrah appears in the middle in its tanzanite form, summoning four snakelings (two on each side). It will then continue on to the starting phase of the next rotation, in which it appears in the middle in its green form and attacks the player with ranged attacks.

===Rotation overview===
[[Zulrah]] will start the fight in one of the four rotations below, chosen at random.

You can tell which rotation Zulrah is in by either the second or fourth phase:
* If the second phase is Zulrah in its '''{{Colour|red|crimson}}''' form, then its third phase will be in its '''{{Colour|#008FFF|tanzanite}}''' form. Afterwards, Zulrah will be in its '''{{Colour|green|green}}''' form in the '''south''' (Rotation 1) or in the '''west''' (Rotation 2).
* If the second phase is Zulrah in its '''{{Colour|green|green}}''' form, then it's in Rotation 3.
* If the second phase is Zulrah in its '''{{Colour|#008FFF|tanzanite}}''' form, then it's in Rotation 4.

The phases below specify Zulrah's position in bold and form by colour, while the "[[Jad]]" phase has been underlined.

Beginners may wish to focus on one specific rotation to learn, immediately hopping worlds to try again if not in that rotation at the start of the second phase. Hopping worlds is possible because the player will not be in combat until the second phase. Rotation 3 is often best for learning since rotations 1 and 2 are ambiguous for longer at the start, and rotation 4 tends to cause more damage.

====Rotation 1 ("Crimson A")====
*Phase 1: Zulrah appears in the '''middle''' in its '''{{Colour|green|green}}''' form, spewing out 4 venom cloud barrages.
*Phase 2: Zulrah appears in the '''middle''' in its '''{{Colour|red|crimson}}''' form, attacking twice with [[Melee]].
*Phase 3: Zulrah appears in the '''middle''' in its '''{{Colour|#008FFF|tanzanite}}''' form, attacking with [[Magic]] and/or [[Ranged]] 4 times.
*Phase 4: Zulrah appears in the '''south''' in its '''{{Colour|green|green}}''' form, attacking with [[Ranged]] 5 times, followed by 2 snakeling orbs, 2 venom cloud barrages, and 2 snakeling orbs.
*Phase 5: Zulrah appears in the '''middle''' in its '''{{Colour|red|crimson}}''' form, attacking twice with [[Melee]].
*Phase 6: Zulrah appears in the '''west''' in its '''{{Colour|#008FFF|tanzanite}}''' form, attacking with both [[Magic]] and/or [[Ranged]] 5 times.
*Phase 7: Zulrah appears in the '''south''' in its '''{{Colour|green|green}}''' form, spewing out 3 venom cloud barrages, followed by 4 snakeling orbs.
*Phase 8: Zulrah appears in the '''south''' in its '''{{Colour|#008FFF|tanzanite}}''' form, attacking with both [[Magic]] and [[Ranged]] 5 times, followed by an alternating series of 5 snakeling orbs and venom cloud barrages.
*<u>Phase 9 ("[[Jad]]" phase): Zulrah appears in the '''west''' in its '''{{Colour|green|green}}''' form, alternating between [[Ranged]] and [[Magic]] attacks 10 times, '''starting with ranged'''. It will then spew out 4 venom cloud barrages.</u>
